Rating: 0
This is NOT black bottom pie. It may be good, but black bottom pie has two layers of filling, one chocolate and the other vanilla flavored with rum or bourbon. The upper layer is traditionally made with gelatin and whipped egg whites folded into the vanilla custard for a chiffon-like layer. Some prefer two layers of custard, chocolate first then vanilla laced with rum or bourbon. It is finished off with whipped cream spread onto the second layer.

