The rave reviews I've gotten on this pie have been beyond compare, even from some tough critics! I use oreos for the crust, 2% milk and half the amount of rum in the filling, double the amount of cream and sugar for the topping (to cover the whole pie), and no rum in the topping. Also, as a fun variation for a party, I've made a bite size version in mini-muffin tins. I used a bit more chocolate in the crust to make sure the mini shells stayed together. I then took them out of the tin after freezing, and filled them liberally. I then used a small star tip to pipe the whipped cream over the top. They present beautifully and are as delicious as the original. Enjoy!

